sql:
SELECT u.username, b.name
FROM users u
INNER JOIN beers b ON u.user_id = b.brewery;

SELECT name 
FROM beers 
WHERE abv > 5;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS user_count
FROM ratings
WHERE rating = 5;

SELECT AVG(rating) AS average_rating
FROM ratings
WHERE beer_id = (SELECT beer_id FROM beers WHERE name = 'beer_name');

SELECT username 
FROM users 
WHERE user_id IN (SELECT user_id FROM ratings WHERE rating = 5);

external_knowledge:
- Frequent reviewers refer to users who have reviewed the beer multiple times. In this case, the threshold for being considered a 'frequent reviewer' is set to a minimum of three reviews;
- The 'first beer' is the beer with `beer_id` 1;
- The usernames are the chosen identifiers for the users in the system.

